      <div class="pf-who-grid" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">1</span><div><strong>Find your stopcock and turn it off</strong><p>For any water leak, the stopcock is your most important control. In most dense victorian back-to-back terraces with a large private rental sector it is under the kitchen sink or in a hallway cupboard. Turn it clockwise to stop all water. This limits damage while we travel to you.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">2</span><div><strong>If you smell gas, leave immediately</strong><p>Do not touch any switches. Open windows and doors. Call <a href="https://cadentgas.com/gas-escapes" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:var(--orange);font-weight:700;">Cadent Gas on 0800 111 999</a> first. Then call us on 07399 676656 once the property is made safe. Our first visit to make a gas escape safe is free.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">3</span><div><strong>For no heating, check boiler pressure</strong><p>If your boiler shows an error code or has cut out, check the pressure gauge. It should read between 1 and 1.5 bar. Below 0.5 bar you can repressurise using the filling loop beneath the boiler. If this does not resolve the fault, call us on 07399 676656.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">4</span><div><strong>Photograph all visible damage</strong><p>Take photos and video of any water damage, leaks or flooding before cleaning up. This documentation supports insurance claims. We also provide our own written report and photographic evidence for your insurer as standard on every Anfield call-out.</p></div></div>
